<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-11-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-11-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="880" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d880">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Crown Prince of Siam</gloss>
                                to President <persName type="to">Roosevelt</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Sumas,
                                        Wash.</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-11-30"><hi rend="italic">November 30,
                                    1902</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Having completed a most interesting tour through the United States, I now
                            beg to take leave of Your Excellency, and to express my heartiest
                            appreciation and gratitude for the very hospitable reception so kindly
                            accorded to me by you and by the officials and the citizens of this
                            friendly country. I assure you that I bear home with me the happiest
                            memories of America and the Americans.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Maha Vajiravudh.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>